PartOfPublication 0..1 -- * subparts PartOfPublication
A PartOfPublication called subparts may have a PartOfPublication. It can have none or just 1.
A PartOfPublication has some PartOfPublications called subparts. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.

EditionOrIssue 1 -- * tableOfContents PartOfPublication
A PartOfPublication called tableOfContents has An EditionOrIssue. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one EditionOrIssue.
An EditionOrIssue has some PartOfPublications called tableOfContents. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a PartOfPublication is created, its EditionOrIssue must be assigned. When a PartOfPublication is deleted, its EditionOrIssue is not deleted and its list of PartOfPublications is decreased. When an EditionOrIssue is deleted, its PartOfPublications are not deleted. They are assigned to another EditionOrIssue.
